{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Clearly, we're living in a moment of crisis."},{"time":3000,"text":"Arguably the financial markets have failed us"},{"time":6000,"text":"and the aid system is failing us,"},{"time":9000,"text":"and yet I stand firmly with the optimists"},{"time":12000,"text":"who believe that there has probably never been a more exciting moment to be alive."},{"time":15000,"text":"Because of some of technologies we've been talking about."},{"time":18000,"text":"Because of the resources, the skills,"},{"time":20000,"text":"and certainly the surge of talent we're seeing all around the world,"},{"time":23000,"text":"with the mindset to create change."},{"time":26000,"text":"And we've got a president who sees himself as a global citizen,"},{"time":31000,"text":"who recognizes that no longer is there a single superpower,"},{"time":34000,"text":"but that we've got to engage in a different way with the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"And by definition, every one of you who is in this room"},{"time":41000,"text":"must consider yourself a global soul,"},{"time":43000,"text":"a global citizen."},{"time":45000,"text":"You work on the front lines. And you've seen the best and the worst"},{"time":47000,"text":"that human beings can do for one another and to one another."},{"time":51000,"text":"And no matter what country you live or work in,"},{"time":53000,"text":"you've also seen the extraordinary things that individuals are capable of,"},{"time":57000,"text":"even in their most ordinariness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Today there is a raging debate"},{"time":63000,"text":"as to how best we lift people out of poverty,"},{"time":67000,"text":"how best we release their energies."},{"time":69000,"text":"On the one hand, we have people that say"},{"time":71000,"text":"the aid system is so broken we need to throw it out."},{"time":74000,"text":"And on the other we have people who say"},{"time":76000,"text":"the problem is that we need more aid."},{"time":78000,"text":"And what I want to talk about is something that compliments both systems."},{"time":82000,"text":"We call it patient capital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"The critics point to the 500 billion dollars spent"},{"time":87000,"text":"in Africa since 1970"},{"time":90000,"text":"and say, and what do we have but environmental degradation"},{"time":93000,"text":"and incredible levels of poverty, rampant corruption?"},{"time":97000,"text":"They use Mobutu as metaphor."},{"time":100000,"text":"And their policy prescription is to"},{"time":104000,"text":"make government more accountable,"},{"time":106000,"text":"focus on the capital markets,"},{"time":108000,"text":"invest, don't give anything away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"On the other side, as I said, there are those who say"},{"time":113000,"text":"the problem is that we need more money."},{"time":115000,"text":"That when it comes to the rich, we'll bail out"},{"time":118000,"text":"and we'll hand a lot of aid,"},{"time":120000,"text":"but when it comes to our poor brethren,"},{"time":122000,"text":"we want little to do with it."},{"time":124000,"text":"They point to the successes of aid:"},{"time":126000,"text":"the eradication of smallpox,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and the distribution of tens of millions"},{"time":131000,"text":"of malaria bed nets and antiretrovirals."},{"time":135000,"text":"Both sides are right."},{"time":137000,"text":"And the problem is that neither side is listening to the other."},{"time":140000,"text":"Even more problematic, they're not listening to"},{"time":143000,"text":"poor people themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"After 25 years of working on issues of"},{"time":147000,"text":"poverty and innovation,"},{"time":149000,"text":"it's true that there are probably no more market-oriented"},{"time":153000,"text":"individuals on the planet"},{"time":155000,"text":"than low-income people."},{"time":157000,"text":"They must navigate markets daily,"},{"time":160000,"text":"making micro-decisions, dozens and dozens,"},{"time":163000,"text":"to move their way through society,"},{"time":165000,"text":"and yet if a single catastrophic health problem"},{"time":168000,"text":"impacts their family,"},{"time":170000,"text":"they could be put back into poverty, sometimes for generations."},{"time":174000,"text":"And so we need both the market"},{"time":176000,"text":"and we need aid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Patient capital works between,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and tries to take the best of both."},{"time":184000,"text":"It's money that's invested in entrepreneurs who know their communities"},{"time":187000,"text":"and are building solutions"},{"time":189000,"text":"to healthcare, water, housing, alternative energy,"},{"time":192000,"text":"thinking of low income people not as passive recipients of charity,"},{"time":197000,"text":"but as individual customers, consumers, clients,"},{"time":200000,"text":"people who want to make decisions in their own lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"Patient capital requires that we have"},{"time":205000,"text":"incredible tolerance for risk,"},{"time":208000,"text":"a long time horizon in terms of allowing those"},{"time":210000,"text":"entrepreneurs time to experiment,"},{"time":212000,"text":"to use the market as the best listening device that we have,"},{"time":216000,"text":"and the expectation of below-market returns,"},{"time":219000,"text":"but outsized social impact."},{"time":222000,"text":"It recognizes that the market has its limitation,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and so patient capital also works"},{"time":228000,"text":"with smart subsidy to extend the benefits of a global economy"},{"time":231000,"text":"to include all people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"Now, entrepreneurs need patient capital"},{"time":235000,"text":"for three reasons."},{"time":237000,"text":"First, they tend to work in markets"},{"time":239000,"text":"where people make one, two, three dollars a day"},{"time":241000,"text":"and they are making all of their decisions within that income level."},{"time":245000,"text":"Second, the geographies in which they work"},{"time":247000,"text":"have terrible infrastructure --"},{"time":249000,"text":"no roads to speak of, sporadic electricity"},{"time":251000,"text":"and high levels of corruption."},{"time":255000,"text":"Third, they are often creating markets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"Even if you're bringing clean water"},{"time":259000,"text":"for the first time into rural villages, it is something new."},{"time":262000,"text":"And so many low-income people"},{"time":264000,"text":"have seen so many failed promises broken"},{"time":268000,"text":"and seen so many quacks and sporadic medicines offered to them"},{"time":272000,"text":"that building trust takes a lot of time,"},{"time":275000,"text":"takes a lot of patience."},{"time":277000,"text":"It also requires being connected to a lot of management assistance."},{"time":281000,"text":"Not only to build the systems,"},{"time":283000,"text":"the business models that allow us"},{"time":285000,"text":"to reach low income people in a sustainable way,"},{"time":287000,"text":"but to connect those business"},{"time":289000,"text":"to other markets, to governments, to corporations --"},{"time":292000,"text":"real partnerships if we want to get to scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"I want to share one story"},{"time":298000,"text":"about an innovation called drip irrigation."},{"time":300000,"text":"In 2002 I met this incredible entrepreneur"},{"time":303000,"text":"named Amitabha Sadangi from India,"},{"time":306000,"text":"who'd been working for 20 years with some of the poorest farmers on the planet."},{"time":310000,"text":"And he was expressing his frustration"},{"time":312000,"text":"that the aid market had bypassed low-income farmers altogether,"},{"time":315000,"text":"despite the fact that 200 million farmers"},{"time":317000,"text":"alone in India make under a dollar a day."},{"time":320000,"text":"They were creating subsidies"},{"time":322000,"text":"either for large farms,"},{"time":324000,"text":"or they were giving inputs to the farmers"},{"time":326000,"text":"that they thought they should use, rather than"},{"time":328000,"text":"that the farmers wanted to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330000,"text":"At the same time Amitabha was"},{"time":332000,"text":"obsessed with this drip irrigation technology"},{"time":335000,"text":"that had been invented in Israel."},{"time":338000,"text":"It was a way of bringing small amounts of water"},{"time":341000,"text":"directly to the stalk of the plant."},{"time":343000,"text":"And it could transform"},{"time":345000,"text":"swaths of desert land into fields of emerald green."},{"time":348000,"text":"But the market also had bypassed low income farmers,"},{"time":352000,"text":"because these systems were both too expensive,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and they were constructed for fields that were too large."},{"time":357000,"text":"The average small village farmer"},{"time":359000,"text":"works on two acres or less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"And so, Amitabha decided that he would take that innovation"},{"time":365000,"text":"and he would redesign it from the perspective"},{"time":367000,"text":"of the poor farmers themselves,"},{"time":369000,"text":"because he spent so many years listening to what they needed"},{"time":372000,"text":"not what he thought that they should have."},{"time":374000,"text":"And he used three fundamental principles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"The first one was miniaturization."},{"time":379000,"text":"The drip irrigation system"},{"time":381000,"text":"had to be small enough that a farmer only had"},{"time":383000,"text":"to risk a quarter acre,"},{"time":386000,"text":"even if he had two,"},{"time":388000,"text":"because it was too frightening, given all that he had at stake."},{"time":391000,"text":"Second, it had to be extremely affordable."},{"time":395000,"text":"In other words, that risk on the quarter acre"},{"time":398000,"text":"needed to be repaid in a single harvest,"},{"time":401000,"text":"or else they wouldn't take the risk."},{"time":403000,"text":"And third, it had to be what Amitabha calls"},{"time":405000,"text":"infinitely expandable."},{"time":407000,"text":"What I mean is with the profits from the first quarter acre,"},{"time":410000,"text":"the farmers could buy a second"},{"time":412000,"text":"and a third and a fourth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"As of today, IDE India, Amitabha's organization,"},{"time":417000,"text":"has sold over 300,000 farmers these systems"},{"time":420000,"text":"and has seen their yields and incomes"},{"time":422000,"text":"double or triple on average,"},{"time":424000,"text":"but this didn't happen overnight."},{"time":427000,"text":"In fact, when you go back to the beginning,"},{"time":429000,"text":"there were no private investors"},{"time":431000,"text":"who would be willing to take a risk on building a new technology"},{"time":434000,"text":"for a market class that made under a dollar a day,"},{"time":437000,"text":"that were known to be some of the most risk-averse people on the planet"},{"time":440000,"text":"and that were working in one of the riskiest sectors, agriculture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"And so we needed grants. And he used significant grants"},{"time":447000,"text":"to research, to experiment, to fail,"},{"time":450000,"text":"to innovate and try again."},{"time":452000,"text":"And when he had a prototype"},{"time":455000,"text":"and had a better understanding of how to market to farmers,"},{"time":458000,"text":"that's when patient capital could come in."},{"time":460000,"text":"And we helped him build a company, for profit,"},{"time":463000,"text":"that would build on IDE's knowledge,"},{"time":466000,"text":"and start looking at sales and exports,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and be able to tap into other kinds of capital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472000,"text":"Secondarily, we wanted to see if we could export"},{"time":475000,"text":"this drip irrigation and bring it into other countries."},{"time":478000,"text":"And so we met Dr. Sono Khangharani in Pakistan."},{"time":482000,"text":"And while, again, you needed patience"},{"time":484000,"text":"to move a technology for the poor"},{"time":486000,"text":"in India into Pakistan,"},{"time":488000,"text":"just to get the permits,"},{"time":490000,"text":"over time we were able to start a company"},{"time":493000,"text":"with Dr. Sono, who runs a large"},{"time":495000,"text":"community development organization in the Thar Desert,"},{"time":498000,"text":"which is one of the remote and poorest areas of the country."},{"time":501000,"text":"And though that company has just started,"},{"time":503000,"text":"our assumption is that there too"},{"time":505000,"text":"we'll see the impact on millions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"But drip irrigation isn't the only innovation."},{"time":510000,"text":"We're starting to see these happening all around the world."},{"time":513000,"text":"In Arusha, Tanzania, A to Z Textile Manufacturing"},{"time":518000,"text":"has worked in partnership with us,"},{"time":520000,"text":"with UNICEF, with the Global Fund,"},{"time":522000,"text":"to create a factory that now employs 7,000 people, mostly women."},{"time":525000,"text":"And they produce 20 million lifesaving bednets"},{"time":527000,"text":"for Africans around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"Lifespring Hospital"},{"time":533000,"text":"is a joint venture between Acumen and the government of India"},{"time":535000,"text":"to bring quality, affordable maternal health care"},{"time":539000,"text":"to low-income women,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and it's been so successful that it's currently building"},{"time":543000,"text":"a new hospital every 35 days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548000,"text":"And 1298 Ambulances decided that it was going to"},{"time":551000,"text":"reinvent a completely broken industry,"},{"time":554000,"text":"building an ambulance service in Bombay"},{"time":556000,"text":"that would use the technology of Google Earth,"},{"time":559000,"text":"a sliding scale pricing system"},{"time":561000,"text":"so that all people could have access,"},{"time":563000,"text":"and a severe and public decision"},{"time":566000,"text":"not to engage in any form of corruption."},{"time":569000,"text":"So that in the terrorist attacks of November"},{"time":571000,"text":"they were the first responder,"},{"time":573000,"text":"and are now beginning to scale, because of partnership."},{"time":575000,"text":"They've just won four government contracts to build off their 100 ambulances,"},{"time":579000,"text":"and are one of the largest and most effective ambulance companies"},{"time":583000,"text":"in India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"This idea of scale is critical."},{"time":587000,"text":"Because we're starting to see these enterprises"},{"time":589000,"text":"reach hundreds of thousands of people. All of the ones I discussed"},{"time":592000,"text":"have reached at least a quarter million people."},{"time":594000,"text":"But that's obviously not enough."},{"time":596000,"text":"And it's where the idea of partnership"},{"time":598000,"text":"becomes so important."},{"time":600000,"text":"Whether it's by finding those innovations"},{"time":602000,"text":"that can access the capital markets,"},{"time":604000,"text":"government itself, or partner with major corporations,"},{"time":607000,"text":"there is unbelievable opportunity for innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"President Obama understands that."},{"time":613000,"text":"He recently authorized the creation of a Social Innovation Fund"},{"time":616000,"text":"to focus on what works in this country,"},{"time":618000,"text":"and look at how we can scale it."},{"time":620000,"text":"And I would submit that it's time to consider"},{"time":623000,"text":"a global innovation fund"},{"time":625000,"text":"that would find these entrepreneurs around the world"},{"time":628000,"text":"who really have innovations, not only for their country,"},{"time":630000,"text":"but ones that we can use in the developed world as well."},{"time":633000,"text":"Invest financial assistance, but also management assistance."},{"time":637000,"text":"And then measure the returns,"},{"time":639000,"text":"both from a financial perspective"},{"time":641000,"text":"and from a social impact perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"When we think about new approaches to aid,"},{"time":647000,"text":"it's impossible not to talk about Pakistan."},{"time":651000,"text":"We've had a rocky relationship with that country"},{"time":653000,"text":"and, in all fairness,"},{"time":655000,"text":"the United States has not always been a very reliable partner."},{"time":658000,"text":"But again I would say that this is our moment"},{"time":662000,"text":"for extraordinary things to happen."},{"time":664000,"text":"And if we take that notion of a global innovation fund,"},{"time":667000,"text":"we could use this time to invest"},{"time":670000,"text":"not directly in government, though we would have government's blessing,"},{"time":673000,"text":"nor in international experts,"},{"time":676000,"text":"but in the many existing entrepreneurs"},{"time":679000,"text":"and civil society leaders"},{"time":681000,"text":"who already are building wonderful innovations"},{"time":685000,"text":"that are reaching people all across the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"People like Rashani Zafar,"},{"time":689000,"text":"who created one of the largest microfinance banks in the country,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and is a real role model for women inside and outside the country."},{"time":696000,"text":"And Tasneem Siddiqui, who developed a way"},{"time":698000,"text":"called incremental housing,"},{"time":700000,"text":"where he has moved 40,000 slum dwellers"},{"time":702000,"text":"into safe, affordable community housing."},{"time":705000,"text":"Educational initiatives like DIL and The Citizen Foundation"},{"time":708000,"text":"that are building schools across the country."},{"time":711000,"text":"It's not hyperbole"},{"time":713000,"text":"to say that these civil society institutions"},{"time":715000,"text":"and these social entrepreneurs"},{"time":717000,"text":"are building real alternatives to the Taliban."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"I've invested in Pakistan for over seven years now,"},{"time":723000,"text":"and those of you who've also worked there"},{"time":725000,"text":"can attest that Pakistanis are an incredibly hard working population,"},{"time":729000,"text":"and there is a fierce upward mobility in their very nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"President Kennedy said that"},{"time":736000,"text":"those who make peaceful revolution impossible"},{"time":740000,"text":"make violent revolution inevitable."},{"time":743000,"text":"I would say that the converse is true."},{"time":745000,"text":"That these social leaders"},{"time":747000,"text":"who really are looking at innovation"},{"time":749000,"text":"and extending opportunity"},{"time":751000,"text":"to the 70 percent of Pakistanis who make less than two dollars a day,"},{"time":754000,"text":"provide real pathways to hope."},{"time":757000,"text":"And as we think about how we construct aid for Pakistan,"},{"time":760000,"text":"while we need to strengthen the judiciary,"},{"time":763000,"text":"build greater stability,"},{"time":765000,"text":"we also need to think about lifting those leaders"},{"time":768000,"text":"who can be role models for the rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"On one of my last visits to Pakistan,"},{"time":774000,"text":"I asked Dr. Sono if he would take me"},{"time":776000,"text":"to see some of the drip irrigation in the Thar Desert."},{"time":779000,"text":"And we left Karachi one morning before dawn."},{"time":782000,"text":"It was about 115 degrees."},{"time":784000,"text":"And we drove for eight hours"},{"time":786000,"text":"along this moonscape-like landscape"},{"time":789000,"text":"with very little color, lots of heat,"},{"time":792000,"text":"very little discussion, because we were exhausted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"And finally, at the end of the journey,"},{"time":796000,"text":"I could see this thin little yellow line across the horizon."},{"time":800000,"text":"And as we got closer, its significance became apparent."},{"time":803000,"text":"That there in the desert"},{"time":805000,"text":"was a field of sunflowers growing seven feet tall."},{"time":808000,"text":"Because one of the poorest farmers on Earth"},{"time":810000,"text":"had gotten access to a technology"},{"time":813000,"text":"that had allowed him to change his own life."},{"time":816000,"text":"His name was Raja,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and he had kind, twinkly hazel eyes"},{"time":820000,"text":"and warm expressive hands"},{"time":823000,"text":"that reminded me of my father."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"And he said it was the first dry season"},{"time":827000,"text":"in his entire life that he hadn't taken"},{"time":830000,"text":"his 12 children and 50 grandchildren"},{"time":832000,"text":"on a two day journey across the desert"},{"time":835000,"text":"to work as day laborers at a commercial farm"},{"time":837000,"text":"for about 50 cents a day."},{"time":839000,"text":"Because he was building these crops."},{"time":841000,"text":"And with the money he earned he could stay this year."},{"time":844000,"text":"And for the first time ever in three generations,"},{"time":847000,"text":"his children would go to school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"We asked him if he would send his daughters as well as his sons."},{"time":853000,"text":"And he said, \"Of course I will."},{"time":855000,"text":"Because I don't want them discriminated against anymore.\""},{"time":860000,"text":"When we think about solutions to poverty,"},{"time":862000,"text":"we cannot deny individuals"},{"time":864000,"text":"their fundamental dignity."},{"time":866000,"text":"Because at the end of the day,"},{"time":868000,"text":"dignity is more important to the human spirit than wealth."},{"time":871000,"text":"And what's exciting is to see so many entrepreneurs across sectors"},{"time":875000,"text":"who are building innovations that recognize"},{"time":878000,"text":"that what people want is freedom"},{"time":880000,"text":"and choice and opportunity."},{"time":882000,"text":"Because that is where dignity really starts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885000,"text":"Martin Luther King said that"},{"time":887000,"text":"love without power is anemic and sentimental,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and that power without love"},{"time":894000,"text":"is reckless and abusive."},{"time":896000,"text":"Our generation has seen both approaches tried,"},{"time":899000,"text":"and often fail."},{"time":901000,"text":"But I think our generation also might be the first"},{"time":904000,"text":"to have the courage to embrace both love and power."},{"time":908000,"text":"For that is what we'll need, as we move forward"},{"time":911000,"text":"to dream and imagine what it will really take"},{"time":914000,"text":"to build a global economy that includes all of us,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and to finally extend that fundamental proposition"},{"time":920000,"text":"that all men are created equal to every human being on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"The time for us to begin innovating"},{"time":927000,"text":"and looking for new solutions, a cross sector, is now."},{"time":931000,"text":"I can only talk from my own experience,"},{"time":933000,"text":"but in eight years of running Acumen fund,"},{"time":937000,"text":"I've seen the power of patient capital."},{"time":939000,"text":"Not only to inspire innovation and risk taking,"},{"time":944000,"text":"but to truly build systems that have created"},{"time":946000,"text":"more than 25,000 jobs"},{"time":948000,"text":"and delivered tens of millions of services and products"},{"time":951000,"text":"to some of the poorest people on the planet."},{"time":954000,"text":"I know it works."},{"time":956000,"text":"But I know that many other kinds of innovation also work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"And so I urge you, in whatever sector you work,"},{"time":962000,"text":"in whatever job you do,"},{"time":964000,"text":"to start thinking about how we might"},{"time":966000,"text":"build solutions that start"},{"time":969000,"text":"from the perspective of those we're trying to help."},{"time":971000,"text":"Rather than what we think that they might need."},{"time":976000,"text":"It will take embracing the world with both arms."},{"time":979000,"text":"And it will take living with the spirit of generosity and accountability,"},{"time":984000,"text":"with a sense of integrity and perseverance."},{"time":988000,"text":"And yet these are the very qualities"},{"time":990000,"text":"for which men and women have been honored"},{"time":992000,"text":"throughout the generations."},{"time":994000,"text":"And there is so much good that we can do."},{"time":997000,"text":"Just think of all those sunflowers in the desert."},{"time":1000000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1002000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}